cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM

This paper proposes a deep learning model for brain structure segmentation from MR images, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) domains. The model utilizes a global context encoding module to capture global context semantics, which involves attention mechanisms and can be related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the model is evaluated on a medical imaging dataset, which can be associated with multimedia (cs.MM).
